 a 90/10 fiber coupler.
 The light that travels down the 90% branch is absorbed by an intensity
 monitor diode.
 The remaining 10% is coupled into a fiber that goes to the apparatus.
 The end of the fiber is carefully directed and positioned next to the isolating
 foil.
 Approximately 5% (XXX) of the light leaving the fiber is reflected from
 the glass/air interface.
 Due to the divergence of the beam (NA XXX, core diameter XXX), less light
 re-enters the fiber core after reflecting from the foil.
 By adjusting the fiber-foil distance, it is possible to tune the internally
 and externally-reflected light to have comparable intensity, maximizing
 the interference contrast.
 In PlateWash, the operating point is ~XXX
