\begin_layout Standard
PlateWash is not a blind experiment.
 It is a precursor to a blind experiment.
 More than half of the science data were taken without a blind, largely
 because we had not discovered a way to monitor the health of the experiment
 without access to data which included the central values of each measurement.
 In the latter half of science data-taking, it became clear that watching
 the errorbars on each cut XXX(terminology?) was sufficient to ensure data
